2019
Early unconfirmed case reports
See also: Epidemiological tracing of severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2
Some medical and environmental analyses in Italy, France and the United States suggest that the virus may have spread for several weeks before December 2019. For its part, a World Health Organization report noted, "These findings are unconfirmed, the methods used are not standardized, and serological tests may have non-specific signals." The World Health Organization urged further investigation of these potential early events.

December
Main Entry: 2019 Coronavirus disease Wuhan outbreak ยง 2019
In December, the first pandemic strain of Newcastle pneumonia, "China Wuhan original virus strain 19A", was introduced.

Post hoc epidemiological investigations pointed to the earliest known case symptoms occurring on December 1, 2019. According to the post hoc recollection of the outpatient physician at the Wuhan City Ufologic Hospital, on December 12, 2019, the hospital saw a 69-year-old male trader at the Wuhan City Huainan Seafood Market who had first appeared with respiratory symptoms, but the fever clinic at this small hospital was unable to confirm these abnormal cases, and after advising the patient to undergo a CT examination to no avail, the outpatient physician had to advise him to go to another better-equipped hospital, a referral time, there was some delay in the discovery of the outbreak. The post hoc study by Huang Chaolin and other scholars said that at the very beginning of the epidemic, the local CDC had concentrated several patients in Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital for isolation and collection of samples and data, of which the earliest data samples had been one taken on December 16, 2019, and sent for testing one after another in the process of attempting treatment. It was not until after the doctors in the emergency department of Wuhan Central Hospital had treated the 65-year-old patient suspected of possible community-acquired pneumonia [Note 1] with various antibiotics that remained ineffective that they finally decided to send the alveolar lavage fluid samples to a third-party testing organization, Guangzhou Weifang Genetics, for testing based on second-generation high-throughput sequencing (NGS) technology so as to try to identify the actual pathogen. Guangzhou Micro Far Genetics in Huangpu, Guangzhou, the first known external laboratory to perform preliminary analysis of the novel coronavirus pathogen, received the sample by courier on December 24 and raised the alarm by finding the SARS coronavirus with approximately 94.5% similarity in the automated mNGS pathogenic microbial interpretation results on December 26.

This unexplained pneumonia was first identified and reported by Dr. Jixian Zhang in the Department of Respiratory and Critical Care Medicine on December 26, 2019, and was suspected to be an infectious disease.

A paper titled "New coronavirus has spread in France at the end of December 2019" was published on May 3, 2020 in the medical journal International Journal of Antimicrobial Agents. Researchers selected 14 intensive care unit cases of influenza illness (ILI) between Dec. 2, 2019, and Jan. 16, 2020, for re-testing for severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 nucleic acid from April 6 to 9 and found a positive sample from a 42-year-old man. The lack of association with China and the absence of a history of foreign travel prior to the onset of the case suggested that severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 had spread in France in late December 2019.

On December 27, 2019, Guangzhou Micro Far Genetics finally assembled a near-complete genome sequence of the unknown virus and shared the data with the Institute of Pathogen Biology, Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences. Later, after making a more detailed comparison and analysis, it was found that the virus was not identical to all known genomic information and might be a novel virus similar to Bat SARS-like coronavirus (BSCV). This data was later submitted to the Global Influenza Data Sharing Initiative website by the Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences on Jan. 11, and the analysis is the earliest dated sample in the database.

On December 30, 2019, the Medical Administration and Medical Management Division of the Wuhan Health and Health Commission, began to send emergency notifications to hospitals at all levels in Wuhan and issued two documents setting out measures for the rescue and treatment of pneumonia of unknown origin [Note 2] when diagnosed. The document flowed out of the health care system in the evening and was widely circulated on the Internet. In the evening, doctors such as Li Wenliang, Liu Wen, and Xielinka disclosed the news related to the outbreak early in an internal WeChat group to provide reference for the hospital's medical staff. Wuhan Central Hospital sent a sample to the Beijing Boao Medical Laboratory on December 27. The laboratory sent the test report back to the hospital on December 30, which listed "SARS coronavirus" (SARS coronavirus) as one of the "high confidence" positive results. Li Wenliang, an ophthalmologist at Wuhan Central Hospital, circulated the test report within the hospital at 17:48 using WeChat to post the news "7 cases of SARS were confirmed at South China Fruit and Seafood Market" and photos of the test report in a group of classmates.

On December 31, 2019, the Wuhan CDC confirmed to the media that the document was true and issued an information circular [Note 3] to begin informing the public about the cases, stating that it was checking what kind of pneumonia it was. On the other hand, the Wuhan Health and Health Commission published the "Information Bulletin of the Wuhan Health and Health Commission on the Current Pneumonia Epidemic in the City", stating that 27 cases had been identified. Both the WHO office in China and the government of the People's Republic of China indicated that they had also informed WHO headquarters of the situation on the same day [Note 4], and that a large number of cases had visited the South China Seafood Market in Wuhan hospitals in mid to late December [Note 5]. On the same day, Taiwan's Agency for Disease Control learned of the suspected SARS outbreak in China through the local media and sent an email to the WHO International Health Regulations Contact Window requesting further information on the outbreak. The email was sent to the WHO International Health Regulations Contact Window requesting further information on the outbreak of atypical pneumonia, mentioning "atypical pneumonia", "patients have been treated in isolation", and confirming the outbreak with the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention in mainland China. Mainland China responded in the evening that the diagnosis was confirmed and informed that experts had been sent to Wuhan to investigate, pointing out that 27 cases of pneumonia had recently been found there, seven of which were in critical condition and had been treated in isolation, with two cases improving. The clinical manifestations provided in the diagnosis, the main symptoms have for fever, a few patients with respiratory distress, showing double lung infiltrative lesions, most of the cases for Wuhan City, Jianghan District, South China Seafood City operators, has not yet found obvious human-to-human transmission phenomenon and health care workers infected. Taiwan on the same day began to direct flights from Wuhan to Taiwan for the entry quarantine.

2020
January

Animation of the global spread of the epidemic from January 12, 2020 to February 29, 2020: countries and regions with confirmed cases in red (shades of color indicate the number of cases) and countries and regions with no confirmed cases in gray.
In the early morning of January 5, 2020, Yongzhen Zhang's team at Fudan University detected a novel SARS-like coronavirus from samples in Wuhan, China, and obtained the full genome sequence of the virus.

On January 6, 2020, a Level II emergency response was activated within the CDC.

On January 7, 2020, Xi Jinping, General Secretary of the CPC Central Committee, presided over the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and put forward requirements for the prevention and control of the epidemic.

On January 9, 2020, the "Wuhan Viral Pneumonia Pathogenic Test Results Preliminary Assessment Panel" officially declared the pathogen as a novel coronavirus.

On January 15, 2020, the CDC switched to a Level 1 emergency response.

At 2200 hours on January 19, 2020, the Wuhan Municipal Health Commission declared that confirmed cases were found among close contacts of confirmed cases, i.e., evidence of human-to-human transmission was found. To prevent further spread of COVID-19 from Wuhan, the center of the outbreak, all traffic in and out of Wuhan was banned from 10:00 a.m. on January 23, 2020 2020, and a day later, the entire Hubei province. In terms of the population involved, this appears to be the largest quarantine (movement restriction) event in human history.


February 2020

Map of the changing distribution of cases in mainland China (as of May 31, 2020 2020)
The number of new cases gradually turned down after the widespread city and village closures and traffic restrictions in many provinces and cities in mainland China in early February 2020
  Number of cured cases
  Number of cases treated in hospital
  Number of death cases
Purple curve: number of new cases per day
During the two weeks from January 31, 2020 to February 12, 2020, a number of cities outside of Hubei Province in China announced the implementation of closed administration. According to incomplete statistics, there are at least 9 primary administrative regions (4 municipalities, 4 provinces, and 1 autonomous region, for a total of 156 secondary administrative regions) with at least 51 secondary administrative regions in other provinces and cities, for a total of 207 (including 26 provincial capitals and sub-provincial cities); among the cities upgraded to fully closed wartime control, there are 2 secondary administrative regions.

On February 1, 2020, an 80-year-old man from Hong Kong was diagnosed with the infection, having boarded the Diamond Princess in Yokohama, Japan, on January 20, 2020, and disembarked at the Kai Tak Cruise Terminal in Hong Kong on January 25, 2020. After the incident, the cruise ship stayed at the port of Yokohama at Daikokubutou from February 4, 2020, and the personnel on board were quarantined in their individual cabins for 14 days before those with relevant symptoms were quarantined by the Japanese Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare. As of March 2, 2020, 705 people on board have been confirmed, including 6 who died after disembarking.

On February 2, 2020, China's National Health Construction Commission notified a cumulative total of 17,205 confirmed cases and 361 deaths in mainland China, with the number of deaths surpassing the total number of deaths in mainland China from SARS.

On February 4, 2020, Hong Kong reported its first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death, then the first death outside of mainland China.

The first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death was reported in the Philippines on February 5, 2020.

On February 12, 2020, Hubei Province changed the number of clinically diagnosed cases from including suspected cases to including confirmed cases for publication, "clinically diagnosed cases" refers to suspected cases with imaging characteristics of pneumonia, as of 24:00 on that day, the cumulative notification of 59,804 confirmed cases, 1,367 deaths, cured and discharged in mainland China 5911 cases; 15152 new cases were confirmed and 254 new deaths were reported on the same day.

In mid-February 2020, a large-scale cluster of infections occurred in the Shintiandi Church in Daegu, South Korea. The first confirmed case of Shintiandi Church member "Patient No. 31" appeared on February 18, 2020. On February 23, 2020, the President of the Republic of Korea, Moon Jae-in, hosted a meeting on countermeasures against the New Coronavirus outbreak at the Seoul Office Building and decided to raise the outbreak alert to the highest level. blockade measures.

The first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death was reported in Japan on February 14, 2020.

The first fatal case of 2019 coronavirus disease was reported in Taiwan on February 16, 2020.

The first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death was reported in Iran on February 19, 2020.

The first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death was reported in South Korea on February 20, 2020.

In late February 2020, several provinces and cities in mainland China were free of new confirmed cases for many days, and many places lowered their emergency response levels and gradually unsealed their cities to facilitate the approval of enterprises to resume work and production, but the cluster phenomenon that occurred immediately after the unsealing of attractions and shopping malls in some areas caused a lot of discussion and concern.

On February 22, 2020, the first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death was reported in Italy.

The first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death was reported in France on February 25, 2020.

On February 26, 2020, WHO Director General Tan Desai said in Geneva that the number of new cases reported outside of China exceeded that of China for the first time on February 25, and that the new outbreak in China has reached a peak "inflection point" and that there are now concerns about global spread, with the number of new cases still rising in Italy and Iran. At the same time, cases exported to neighboring countries have begun to be detected, and the outbreak has spread to all continents inhabited by humans.

On February 27, 2020, as the epidemic continues to intensify in Japan and in order to prevent the further spread of New Crown Pneumonia in Japan, Prime Minister (PM) Shinzo Abe made a request to suspend classes at elementary, junior high and high schools nationwide at a meeting of the Government Countermeasures Headquarters held on the afternoon of the 27th. From March 2, 2020, public elementary, junior high and high schools nationwide will be temporarily closed for the holiday until the end of spring break. The government has also issued a circular to sports and cultural organizations to suspend all major events and public performances until March 15, 2020.

On February 29, 2020, World Health Organization (WHO) Director General Ted Tam announced in Geneva that the global risk level for the outbreak had been raised from "high" to "very high". The first death from 2019 coronavirus disease is reported in the United States.

In February 2020, cases of novel coronavirus disease were detected in other countries in the following order: in Belgium on February 4, 2020; in Egypt on February 14, 2020; in Iran on February 19, 2020; in Lebanon, Israel on February 21, 2020; in Iraq on February 22, 2020; in Afghanistan, Kuwait, Bahrain, Oman on February 24, 2020. February 25, 2020 Austria, Croatia, Switzerland, Algeria, Brazil; February 26, 2020 Pakistan, Georgia, Romania, North Macedonia, Greece, Norway; February 27, 2020 Denmark, Estonia, Belarus, Netherlands, San Marino, Nigeria; February 28, 2020 Azerbaijan, Lithuania, Monaco, Iceland Mexico, New Zealand; February 29, 2020 Kada, Luxembourg, Ireland, Ecuador, a total of 37 countries and regions.

March 2020

Distribution of cumulative confirmed cases by country in Europe
The European outbreak has been in progress since March 2020, and the WHO declared on March 13, 2020 that Europe is now the epicenter of a pandemic plague.
  More than 10,000 confirmed cases exist in the area
  1000-9999 confirmed cases exist in the region
  100-999 confirmed cases exist in the region
  10-99 confirmed cases exist in the region
  Presence of 1-9 confirmed cases in the region
In March 2020, the second pandemic strain of Newcastle pneumonia, "mutant virus strain D614G," was introduced.

On March 1, 2020, the first confirmed cases of 2019 coronavirus disease were reported in Armenia, the Czech Republic, and Dominica.

First deaths of 2019 coronavirus disease reported in Thailand, Australia on March 1, 2020

On March 2, 2020, the first confirmed cases of 2019 coronavirus disease were reported in Andorra, Indonesia, Jordan, Latvia, Morocco, Portugal, Saudi Arabia, Senegal, and Tunisia.

On March 3, 2020, the first confirmed cases of 2019 coronavirus disease were reported in Argentina, Chile, Liechtenstein, and Ukraine.

First case of 2019 coronavirus disease death reported in Iraq on March 3, 2020.

On March 4, 2020, the outbreak spread rapidly in Italy and the Italian government decided to close all schools across the country for two weeks from now. It also closed all other stores except pharmacies and supermarkets. As of March 3, 2020, there were 2,036 confirmed cases throughout Italy, of which 83 people recovered and were discharged from the hospital.

On the same day, the first confirmed cases of 2019 coronavirus disease were reported in Hungary, Poland and Slovenia.

On March 5, 2020, Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe announced that all passengers entering Japan from China and South Korea will be sent to a designated quarantine facility for 14 days starting at 00:00 a.m. on March 9, 2020, and will not be allowed to travel on public transportation.

On the same day, the first confirmed cases of 2019 coronavirus disease were reported in Bosnia and Herzegovina, Palestine and South Africa.

The first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death was reported in the United Kingdom on March 5, 2020.

On March 6, 2020, the first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death was reported in the Netherlands.

On March 7, 2020, the first confirmed cases of 2019 coronavirus disease were reported in Maldives, Malta, Moldova, and Paraguay.

On March 7, 2020, the first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death was reported in Argentina.

On March 8, 2020, Albania, Bangladesh, and Bulgaria reported the first confirmed cases of 2019 coronavirus disease.

First death from 2019 coronavirus disease reported in Spain and Egypt on March 8, 2020.

On March 9, 2020, Brunei, Cyprus and Panama reported the first confirmed cases of 2019 coronavirus disease.

First deaths from 2019 coronavirus disease reported in Lebanon, Germany, and Canada on March 9, 2020.

On March 10, 2020, Italy extended its blockade quarantine measures to the entire country. The President of the Italian Council of Ministers (Prime Minister) Antonio Conte announced restrictions on the movement of people throughout Italy as of that date, and Italians were told not to leave their homes unless there were urgent health or work reasons. As of that date, there were 9,172 confirmed cases and 463 deaths throughout Italy.

On the same day, the first confirmed cases of 2019 coronavirus disease were reported in Bolivia, Burkina Faso, Democratic Republic of the Congo, Jamaica, Mongolia, Northern Cyprus and Turkey.

First case of 2019 coronavirus disease death reported in Belgium, Morocco on March 10, 2020.

On the evening of March 11, 2020, U.S. President Donald Trump delivered a nationally televised address announcing a 30-day moratorium on "all travel from Europe (except the United Kingdom) to the United States" beginning on March 13, 2020. The ban on entry list.

On the same day, St. Vincent and the Grenadines and Trinidad and Tobago reported the first confirmed cases of 2019 coronavirus disease.

On March 11, 2020, Indonesia, Bulgaria, Albania, Sweden, Ireland, Panama, and Guyana reported the first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death.

On March 12, 2020, Mi Feng, spokesperson of the National Health and Wellness Commission of the People's Republic of China, said that 15 new confirmed cases (including 8 cases in Wuhan and 6 cases imported from abroad) were diagnosed in mainland China on March 11, 2020, and the number of new cases in Wuhan dropped to single digits. The above information suggests that the peak of the current epidemic in mainland China has generally passed, the number of new cases is continuing to decline, and the epidemic overall remains at a low level.

On the same day, St. Vincent and the Grenadines and Trinidad and Tobago reported the first confirmed cases of 2019 coronavirus disease.

On March 12, 2020, India, Azerbaijan, Greece, Norway, Denmark, Poland, Liechtenstein, Austria, Algeria, and Sudan reported the first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death.

It is a sad and significant statistic that more than 132,000 cases of COVID-19 have now been reported to WHO by 123 countries and territories, and the death toll has exceeded 5,000, WHO Director-General Tandse said at a regular press conference on March 13, 2020. Europe has now become the epicenter of the pandemic plague, with more cases and deaths reported than the rest of the world combined, except for China. This comes after a number of countries, including Denmark, Poland, Spain, Latvia, the Czech Republic, Hungary, Argentina, Ecuador, the Philippines and the United States, declared states of emergency in the previous week.

On the same day, the first confirmed cases of 2019 coronavirus disease were reported in Antigua and Barbuda, Ethiopia, Gabon, Ghana, Guatemala, Guinea, Kazakhstan, Kenya, Kosovo, Puerto Rico, St. Lucia, Sudan, Suriname, the U.S. Virgin Islands, Uruguay and Venezuela.

First deaths from 2019 coronavirus disease reported in Slovenia, Ukraine, and Ecuador on March 13, 2020.

On the evening of March 14, 2020, the President of the Spanish government (Prime Minister), Josรฉ Sรกnchez, announced a nationwide "city closure" for 15 days to contain the Newcastle pneumonia outbreak, prohibiting all people and private vehicles from going outside except for work, food and medicine purchases, medical treatment and other essential and emergency situations. At the same time, all public places except supermarkets, pharmacies, barber stores and other essential products and services were closed. Schools nationwide were closed and replaced with online classes, and passenger transportation capacity was reduced. The same day Portuguese Prime Minister Costa announced that schools would be closed. This initiative, which will last until April 9, 2020, will affect 1.6 million students; in Belgium, in addition to school closures, only stores providing essential services will remain open from March 14, 2020.

On March 14, 2020, Polish Prime Minister Morawiecki said that Poland would close its borders for 10 days, and that the Polish government would allow only domestic lines to continue to operate in terms of rail and air traffic.

On the same day, the Central African Republic, Congo, Equatorial Guinea, Swaziland, Mauritania, Namibia, Rwanda and Seychelles reported the first confirmed cases of 2019 coronavirus disease.

On March 15, 2020, Lithuania bans all foreigners from entering the country.

On the same day, the first confirmed cases of 2019 coronavirus disease were reported in the Bahamas, Guam and Uzbekistan.

March 15, 2020 First deaths of 2019 coronavirus disease reported in Turkey, Hungary, Guatemala

On March 16, 2020, Argentina announced that its borders would be closed for the next 15 days.

On March 16, 2020, at 8:00 am, Germany will close its borders with France, Austria and Switzerland.

On March 16, 2020, the Czech government announced a total ban on the movement of people, and the Norwegian government closed all ports of entry and exit and airports. Latveria and Estonia have also taken measures to restrict the movement of people. The Russian government announced the closure of the country's borders with Poland and Norway and a ban on the entry of foreigners at these border crossings. Morocco cancelled civil and shipping traffic with about 20 countries, including Germany.

On the same day, the first confirmed cases of 2019 coronavirus disease were reported in Benin, Greenland, Liberia, Somalia and Tanzania.

