April 2020
At a media briefing on the outbreak on April 1, 2020, WHO Director-General Desai Tan expressed deep concern about the rapid escalation of infections and their global spread. In the past five weeks, the number of new cases has increased almost exponentially, in almost every country, territory and area, said Tan Desai. In the past week, the number of deaths has more than doubled. In the next few days, it will reach one million confirmed cases and 50,000 deaths. Although relatively few confirmed cases have been reported in Africa, Central America and South America, COVID-19 could have serious social, economic and political consequences for these regions.

First case of 2019 coronavirus disease death reported in Oman, Botswana on April 1, 2020.

As of 4 p.m. EDT on April 2, 2020, there were more than one million new cases of coronary pneumonia and more than 50,000 deaths worldwide.

On April 2, 2020, the Russian government decided to extend the paid non-working week until April 30, 2020. Thirty U.S. states have been approved to declare a "state of major disaster" and several states have declared "home quarantine orders". The Italian government has decided to extend all previous restrictions on the control of the new crown outbreak until April 13, 2020.

On the same day, Malawi reported the first confirmed case of 2019 coronavirus disease.

On April 2, 2020, the first deaths from 2019 coronavirus disease were reported in Kyrgyzstan, Libya, Senegal, and Zambia.

On April 3, 2020, the State Council of the People's Republic of China issued a proclamation stating that in order to express the deep mourning of the martyrs and deceased compatriots who died in the national struggle against the epidemic, it was decided to hold national mourning activities on April 4, 2020 2020, the Qingming Festival. During this period, the nation and embassies and consulates abroad will mourn at half mourning and stop public entertainment activities. 2020 2020 From 10:00 a.m. on April 4, 2020, the nation will observe three minutes of silence, cars, trains and ships will sound their horns, and air defense sirens will sound. Most TV channels across the country turned their station emblems to gray and rebroadcast programs from CCTV's comprehensive channels, and some websites also turned their main colors to gray.

First case of 2019 coronavirus disease death reported in Latvia, Suriname, April 3, 2020

On April 4, 2020, with the number of confirmed cases in the United States topping 300,000, Trump warned at a White House press briefing the same day that the United States would see the toughest time of the new coronavirus epidemic in the next two weeks, and predicted a spike in deaths: "Unfortunately," in the next two weeks, " There will be a lot of deaths" and "more if they don't cooperate with the measures to fight the epidemic."

First case of 2019 coronavirus disease death reported in Georgia, Liberia on April 4, 2020.

On the same day, Spanish Prime Minister Sรกnchez extended the embargo until April 25, 2020, and the United Kingdom saw another record high of 708 deaths from the new coronavirus, for a cumulative total of 4,313 deaths.

The first confirmed case of 2019 coronavirus disease was reported in South Sudan on April 5, 2020.

On April 5, 2020, Kuwait, Ethiopia, and St. Kitts and Nevis reported their first cases of 2019 coronavirus disease deaths.

The first confirmed case of 2019 coronavirus disease was reported in Sao Tome and Principe on April 6, 2020.

First case of 2019 coronavirus disease death reported in Benan, Haiti, April 6, 2020.

In the evening of April 7, 2020, Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe announced at a meeting of the Japanese government's Headquarters for Countermeasures against Novel Coronavirus Infection that seven prefectures - Tokyo, Kanagawa, Saitama, Chiba, Osaka, Hyogo, and Fukuoka - are in an emergency situation that will last until May 6, 2020. Abe said that the number of patients in Japan is increasing exponentially recently, and at the current pace, the number of patients will increase to 10,000 in 2 weeks and more than 80,000 in 1 month.

First case of 2019 coronavirus disease death reported in Malawi, Belize on April 7, 2020

On the same day, the first confirmed cases of 2019 coronavirus disease were reported in Abkhazia and the Republic of Artsakh.

The first confirmed case of 2019 coronavirus disease was reported in Yemen on April 10, 2020.

On April 11, 2020, the cumulative number of deaths worldwide exceeded 100,000.

