The first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death was reported in Guinea on April 15, 2020.

The first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death was reported in Swaziland on April 16, 2020.

The first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death was reported in French Guiana on April 20, 2020.

First case of 2019 coronavirus disease death reported in Equatorial Guinea on April 21, 2020.

On April 28, 2020, the number of people diagnosed with New Coronary Pneumonia in the United States exceeded 1 million, making it the first country in the world to have more than 1 million confirmed cases.

April 28, 2020 - Researchers at India's National Institute of Biomedical Genomics have found that Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome coronavirus 2 has mutated into at least 10 different variants, with one variant called A2a being more likely to spread between people than others, according to the Daily Star website.

The first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death was reported in Lion Rock on April 23, 2020.

