May 2020
The first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death was reported in Tajik on May 2, 2020.

The first confirmed case of 2019 coronavirus disease was reported in South Ossetia on May 6, 2020.

From May 10, 2020 to May 11, 2020, the Wuhan Health Commission notified six new cases, all of which came from the Sanmin neighborhood on Changqing Street in the East-West Lake District of Wuhan, which led to the reclosure of the neighborhood. On the evening of May 11, 2020, Wuhan City issued an "Urgent Notice on the City's New Coronavirus Nucleic Acid Screening", which required all neighborhoods in the city to conduct universal testing for up to ten days. from May 12, 2020, the neighborhoods in Wuhan City began their respective neighborhoods' universal testing for up to ten days one after another.

On May 13, 2020, Lesotho reported the first confirmed case of 2019 coronavirus disease, and all countries in Africa reported confirmed cases.

The first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death was reported in South Sudan on May 14, 2020.

May 16, 2020 First death from 2019 coronavirus disease reported in Nepal, Madagascar

The two-day World Health Assembly (WHA) opened in Geneva, Switzerland, on May 18, 2020. Chinese President Xi Jinping pledged $2 billion in aid to countries around the world over the next two years in a teleconference table at the opening of the conference.

On May 20, 2020, Australia's proposal for an independent investigation into the traceability of the pneumonia virus was endorsed by 194 member states and passed at the World Health Assembly. Australia's proposal for an independent investigation had been opposed by China before the vote, and even after more than 110 countries expressed support for an independent investigation into the virus at the World Health Assembly, Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhao Lijian reiterated Beijing's position at a regular press conference, saying it was too early to conduct such an investigation while the outbreak was still unfolding. Australia's insistence on pushing for an independent investigation has led to a deterioration in relations with China. China's ambassador to Australia, Cheng Jingye, warned the Australian government that Australia's approach would lead to discontent among Chinese consumers and that Australia's wine, beef and other agricultural products and tourism would be boycotted. When the proposal was passed by the WHO, the Chinese Embassy in Australia criticized Australia's attitude of pushing for an independent investigation with a consciousness of victory as a "joke".

The first case of death from 2019 coronavirus disease was reported in the Central African Republic on May 23, 2020.

First case of 2019 coronavirus disease death reported in Mozambique on May 25, 2020.

The first case of 2019 coronavirus disease death was reported in Western Sahara on May 26, 2020.

On May 27, 2020, the number of deaths from coronavirus disease in the United States exceeded 100,000 in 2019, making it the first country in the world to have more than 100,000 deaths.

In May, 2019 coronavirus disease had a massive outbreak in Russia, Brazil, India and Peru, with 344,000 confirmed cases in Russia, 349,000 in Brazil, 131,000 in India and 115,000 in Peru as of May 24, 2020.

Due to the violent law enforcement death of black American George Floyd by white police officer Derek Shovan, the wave of protests over the death of George Floyd sparked the largest unrest in the United States in 30 years, and the number of confirmed cases is on the rise. The black victim, who lost his job because of the epidemic, was later diagnosed with the disease in the autopsy report as well.

